    "summary": {
      "value": "Use Might for Magic Checks, and treat weapons relying on Might as being arcane."
    },
    "description": "<blockquote><p><strong>Requirements:</strong> you must have mastered one or more Classes among <strong>Chimerist</strong>, <strong>Darkblade</strong>, <strong>Esper</strong> (see <strong>Techno Fantasy</strong>, page <strong>150</strong>), <strong>Fury</strong>, and <strong>Wayfarer</strong></p></blockquote><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you perform a Magic Check for a spell or Ritual, you may replace </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>one</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">of the Attributes with </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Might</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">(such as </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>【</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>MIG + MIG</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>】</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">for a Chimerism Ritual).<br />As long as the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Accuracy</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">formula of a weapon you have equipped includes </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Might</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, you may treat that weapon as also belonging to the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>arcane</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Category for the purpose of Skills and effects that require it.</span></p>",
